com.pb.sawdust.tabledata.basic

Class ReadOnlyWrappedDataTable

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pb.sawdust.tabledata.basic.WrappedDataTable
      • com.pb.sawdust.tabledata.basic.FixedSizeDataTable
        • com.pb.sawdust.tabledata.basic.ReadOnlyWrappedDataTable
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataTable, java.lang.Iterable<DataRow>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    OrderedDataTable

    public class ReadOnlyWrappedDataTable
extends FixedSizeDataTable
    The ReadOnlyWrappedDataTable class provides a data table wrapper whose contents cannot be modified. Since this class only wraps the underlying data table, changes to that data table (if allowed) will be reflected through to this data table instance.

      • setPrimaryKey

        public <K> boolean setPrimaryKey(TableKey<K> primaryKey)
        Set the primary key for this data table. If successful, this will replace the current primary key specified on the table. Because there is no technical restriction that the specified key has been built on (or refers to) this data table, it is preferable to use the DataTable.setPrimaryKey(String) method to set the table's primary key. This method is intending for primary key switching convenience and efficiency and, as such, the key index will not be rebuilt when this method is called.
        Specified by:
        setPrimaryKey in interface DataTable
        Overrides:
        setPrimaryKey in class WrappedDataTable
        Parameters:
        primaryKey - The key to set as this table's primary key.
        Returns:
        true if the key was set successfully, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - always, since this data table is read-only.

      • setPrimaryKey

        public boolean setPrimaryKey(java.lang.String columnLabel)
        Set the primary key for this data table by specifying the key column. If successful, this will replace the current primary key specified on the table. If the specified column is not found in the table, then this mehtod will return false.
        Specified by:
        setPrimaryKey in interface DataTable
        Overrides:

        Throws:
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - always, since this data table is read-only.
